Skip py_image_layer venv interpreter shims.

rules_python 2.0.x creates .venv/bin/python* shims as symlinks to the
interpreter repository. The py_image_layer default mtree split treats these as
regular files, but tar actions do not have the symlink target as an input and
fail when reading the mtree. The actual interpreter is already captured by the
interpreter layer, so skip these generated shims.

diff --git a/py/private/py_image_layer.bzl b/py/private/py_image_layer.bzl
--- a/py/private/py_image_layer.bzl
+++ b/py/private/py_image_layer.bzl
@@ -84,4 +84,10 @@ awk < $< 'BEGIN {
     if ($$1 ~ "\\.whl$$") {
         next
     }
+    # Exclude generated venv interpreter shims. The actual interpreter is
+    # grouped separately by default_layer_groups, while these shims can be
+    # symlinks to external repos that are not tar action inputs.
+    if ($$1 ~ "\\.venv/bin/python([0-9.]*)?$$") {
+        next
+    }
     # Move everything under the specified root
